<p>Tested with Sony Aqua M2 running Android 4.4.4:</p>  <p>My cordova application using the Apache's camera plugin keeps crashing. With lower quality options it happens a bit more rarely like every 30 photos and with 100% quality &amp; no width or height set it can happen like for every 3rd photo.</p>  <p>Camera settings: </p>  <pre><code>navigator.camera.getPicture(onSuccess, onFail,             {                 sourceType: Camera.PictureSourceType.CAMERA,                 correctOrientation: true,                 quality: 50,                 allowEdit: false,                 targetWidth: 1200,                 destinationType: Camera.DestinationType.FILE_URI,                 encodingType: Camera.EncodingType.JPEG,                 saveToPhotoAlbum: false             }         ); </code></pre>  <p>The phone keeps saving data somewhere. When I check settings/apps/my app it show there is saved data of about the amount of a photo to the storage. Even when I delete the file from the URL camera returns like this: </p>  <pre><code>    $scope.removePhotoFromDeviceMemory = function (uriToPhoto) {         $scope.filesystemImageSuccess = function (fileEntry) {             console.log("REMOVING POHOT FROM DEVICE")             console.log(fileEntry);              function removeSuccesful() {                 console.log("IMAGE REMOVED");             }              function removingFailed() {                 console.log("IMAGE REMOVING FAILED");              }              fileEntry.remove(removeSuccesful, removingFailed);           }         $scope.filesystemImageFail = function () {             console.log("fuuu");         }         window.resolveLocalFileSystemURL(uriToPhoto, $scope.filesystemImageSuccess, $scope.filesystemImageFail)     } </code></pre>  <p>Where else can the photo be stored? </p>  <p>The app crashes like this: </p>  <pre><code>E/AndroidRuntime(24879): FATAL EXCEPTION: main E/AndroidRuntime(24879): Process: com.conexbird, PID: 24879 E/AndroidRuntime(24879): jav